data.content:
# EF Core 10 Breaking Changes for Your Code

## 1. `SetProperty` Expression Tree — Value Must Be a Lambda

In EF Core 10, the `SetProperty` overload accepting a raw `TProperty` value was removed. The value argument must now be an `Expression<Func<TSource, TProperty>>` (a lambda), even for constants.

**Fix:** Wrap `Expression.Constant("foo")` in a lambda:

```csharp
var sParam = Expression.Parameter(typeof(Blog), "b2");
var valueLambda = Expression.Lambda<Func<Blog, string>>(
    Expression.Constant("foo"), sParam);

setters = Expression.Lambda<Func<SetPropertyCalls<Blog>, SetPropertyCalls<Blog>>>(
    Expression.Call(
        instance: setters.Body,
        methodName: nameof(SetPropertyCalls<Blog>.SetProperty),
        typeArguments: new[] { typeof(string) },
        arguments: new Expression[]
        {
            Expression.Lambda<Func<Blog, string>>(
                Expression.Property(blogParameter, nameof(Blog.Name)), blogParameter),
            valueLambda  // was: Expression.Constant("foo")
        }),
    setters.Parameters);
```

---

## 2. Complex Types — Default Column Naming Changed

EF Core 10 changed the default column naming for complex type properties from `{TypeName}_{Property}` to `{NavigationName}_{Property}`. Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` share a CLR type, existing columns will no longer match.

**Fix:** Explicitly configure column names to preserve the old mapping:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
        // ... other properties
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested: explicitly set column names
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, a =>
        {
            a.Property(x => x.City).HasColumnName("Payment_BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

Or generate a new migration if you're OK renaming the columns.

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — New `CommandSource` Parameter

EF Core 10 added a `CommandSource` parameter to the interface methods.

**Fix:**

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        CommandSource commandSource)   // <-- new parameter
    { /* logging */ }
}
```

Update all implemented methods on the interface to include the new `CommandSource` parameter (it's an enum indicating whether the command originated from `SaveChanges`, `LinqQuery`, `ExecuteUpdate`, etc.).
